Bangladesh

   © Kathleen Prior pour Action contre la Faim
   (BUTTON)
   (BUTTON)
   Muk Kashim, aged 8, from Rammiya Bil, Moungdaw. Muk fled fighting in
   his village, with his mother, siblings and grandparents. Now, they live
   in Balukhali refugee camp. At an Action Against Hunger food
   distribution, Muk collected bags of biryani. Action Against Hunger have
   given the family food even day since they arrived in the camp one week
   ago, and provided the first meal they ate after they crossed the
   border. Muk said:“I fled with my mother. My father was killed by the
   military, they cut his throat. “I already had some food from [Action
   Against Hunger] this morning. So I am not hungry anymore. We didn’t
   have anything to eat when we were walking here. But I feel better
   now.“I couldn't bring anything from home. I had to leave everything
   behind. My home was burned down.”

