   Notre intervention au Mali

   In 2018 the situation in Mali was dominated by the presidential
   elections held between July and August.

   As in most of the countries of the Sahel, 2018 has been a year of
   crisis due to the shortage of pastures, which are fundamental to the
   livelihoods of most of the population, especially in the centre and
   north of the country. Likewise, the conflict in the north is already
   surpassing the borders of Niger and Burkina Faso. A solution or
   improvement of the situation is not expected any time soon.

   Despite the difficulties imposed on our operations by the security
   context, we have managed to  aintain a good level of access in our
   intervention areas this year.

   ML02
   Type of intervention
     * Nutrition and Health
     * Food Security and Resources of Existence
     * Water, Sanitation and Hygiene
     * Risk and Disaster Management

   Country key figures

   Number of beneficiaries : 2 342 881

   Population : 15,3 millions

   Life expectancy : 54,6 years old

   Human Development Index : 182/187

   Operational Volume : 10 969 460 €

   Financing

   Gouvernement de Navarra, EC (ECHO et Fonds Européen de Développement),
   AECID, UNICEF, OFDA, Mairie de Zaragoza, Agence Andalouse de
   Coopération, ACF

   ML_NUT_2018_TobyMadden_181 © Toby Madden pour Action contre la Faim

